                <note rend="inline" type="source">811.3393/4–2449: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Consul General at Shanghai</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Cabot</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Shanghai</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1949-04-24T13:00:00+08:00"
                            >April 24, 1949—1 p. m.</date>
                        <lb/> [Received April 24—1:14 a. m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>1319. Department will, of course, appreciate that change in Navy plans (Deptel
                    733, April 23,) for second time, and at more critical moment than when AAG<note
                        n="66" xml:id="d1273fn66">Army Advisory Group.</note> announced in early
                    December its intention to withdraw, has completely scuttled emergency evacuation
                    plan for American community. I am calling a meeting of community leaders
                    tomorrow to discuss what measures, if any, civilians wish to take to assure so
                    far as possible their mutual protection.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Cabot</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
